<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer15059868173499225355">After working for Time Magazine as a researcher, reporter, and Miami bureau chief, García turned to writing fiction. Her first novel, <i>Dreaming in Cuban</i> (1992), received critical acclaim and was a finalist for the National Book Award. She has since published her novels <i>The Agüero Sisters</i> (1997) and <i>Monkey Hunting</i> (2003), and has edited books of Cuban and other Latin American literature. Her fourth </span>
  <span id="freeText15059868173499225355" style="display:none">After working for Time Magazine as a researcher, reporter, and Miami bureau chief, García turned to writing fiction. Her first novel, <i>Dreaming in Cuban</i> (1992), received critical acclaim and was a finalist for the National Book Award. She has since published her novels <i>The Agüero Sisters</i> (1997) and <i>Monkey Hunting</i> (2003), and has edited books of Cuban and other Latin American literature. Her fourth novel, <i>A Handbook to Luck</i>, was released in hardcover in 2007 and came out in paperback in April 2008.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15059868173499225355" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
